cs.CR, cs.GT, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.IT 

This paper deals with the problem of estimating a sensitive statistic on a population while taking into account individuals' privacy concerns and costs. This falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR) as well as game theory (cs.GT) since individuals are rational and may misreport their costs. The paper also proposes a mechanism for approaching individuals randomly, which involves data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper deals with statistical estimation, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
